Diabetes

2022-10-6

Source:

https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Early+stage+diabetes+risk+prediction+dataset.

About

Data has been collected using direct questionnaires from the patients of Sylhet Diabetes Hospital in Sylhet, Bangladesh and approved by a doctor.

Attribute Information:

  1. Age: 20-65

  2. Gender 1. Male, 0. Female

  3. PolyU: (Polyuria) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  4. PolyD: (Polydipsia) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  5. WLoss: (Sudden Weight Loss) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  6. Weak: (Weakness) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  7. PolyP: (Polyphagia) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  8. GThrush: (Genital Thrush) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  9. VB: (Visual Blurring) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  10. Itch: (Itching) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  11. Irritability: 1. Yes, 0.No.

  12. DHeal: (Delayed Healing) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  13. PP: (Partial Paresis) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  14. Stiff: (Muscle Stiffness) 1. Yes, 0.No.

  15. Alopecia: 1. Yes, 0.No.

  16. Obesity: 1. Yes, 0.No.

  17. class: Positive, Negative.

library(ggplot2)

diabetes <- read_xlsx("D:/FOSSEE/Dataset/Data Set/Logical/Diabetes/Diabetes.xlsx")
class0 <- subset(diabetes,class=='Positive')
class1 <- subset(diabetes,class=='Negative')

1) Age

age0<-class0$Age
hist(age0, main= "Class 0", col = "blue")
age1<-class1$Age
hist(age1, main= "Class 1", col = "red")
age<-diabetes$Age
hist(age, main= "Both Classes", col = "green")

2) Gender

p <- class0 %>%
    count(Gender)
ggplot(p, aes(x=(Gender),y=n)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "blue", stat = "identity")+
  geom_text(aes(label=n), vjust =-0.3)+
  ggtitle("Class 0")

p <- class1 %>%
    count(Gender)
ggplot(p, aes(x=(Gender),y=n)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "red", stat = "identity")+
  geom_text(aes(label=n), vjust =-0.3)+
  ggtitle("Class 1")

p <- diabetes %>%
    count(Gender)
